text: Młoszowa [] is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Trzebinia in Chrzanów County, Lesser Poland Voivodeship in southern Poland. It is southeast of Trzebinia, east of Chrzanów, and west of the regional capital Kraków. In 2004, 2,610 people lived there. Category:Villages in Lesser Poland Voivodeship
title: Młoszowa
